result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (7th, 8th or 9th) and Operating w/ PAC (7th, 8th or 9th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (7th, 8th or 9th) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (7th, 8th or 9th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Gary Alan Morrison was found guilty of OWI (7th, 8th or 9th), a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 9:15 AM Defendant Gary Alan Morrison appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Patti l Wabitsch in court for Gary Alan Morrison.  Attorney Douglas J Drexler in court for State of Wisconsin. State moves to dismiss Counts 2 & 3. Court dismisses Counts 2 & 3 upon State's motion.  Defendant pleads no contest to Count 1. Plea is freely, voluntarily, and intelligently given. Constitutional rights read and waived. Court finds defendant guilty due to no contest plea. Statement by State. Statement by Attorney Wabitsch. Statement by defendant. Statement by Court. Court sentences defendant to 10 years prison, 5 years initial confinement and 5 years extended supervision, eligible for programing after 4 years of confinement if he hasn't already completed, drivers license revoked for lifetime, IID, costs ordered and can be paid out of prison accounts or wages. Submit DNA sample. Appeal rights given. Adj. 9:52am jjm
